"&#xa0;Confederation of British Industry—Written evidenceThe CBI is the UK’s leading business organisation, speaking for some 240,000 businesses that together employ around a third of the private sector workforce.  With offices across the UK as well as representation in Brussels, Washington, Beijing and Delhi th\ne CBI communicates the British business voice around the world. \nThe CBI welcomes the opportunity to contribute to \nthe \ninquiry into the draft Finance Bill 2014 which was published on 10 December 2013\n. \n \ni) Taxation of Partnerships Overview\nThe proposed rules do not meet the stated policy objectives \nThe consultation process\nii) New approach to tax policy making Greater predictability\nGreater stability\nPromoting simplicity\nGreater scrutiny\nSupporting transparency\nAppendix A: Additional comments on the Taxation of PartnershipsSome additional views \nhave been\n raised \nby CBI members on the taxation of partner\nships and \nwhile these do not represent consensus comments of the CBI Tax Committee, we feel that they are important to share these as part of the \nEconomic Affairs Committee’s\n enquiry.\nDisguised remuneration – design of legislation and economic impact\nProfit allocation in mixed partnerships\nJanuary 2014\n https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/193239/Corporation_tax_road_map.pdf \n http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/documents/digitalasset/dg_188582.pdf\n"